                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/639.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Messrs.
                            <gloss type="to">Kuhn, Loeb and Company</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s January 6 and your reply same date. It is hoped that
                    fiscal agents and attorneys have reached agreement about payment Liberian
                    interest, and that Department may soon be able to reply to telegram received
                    from American Minister Monrovia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
